  "description": "<p>\n\t<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://news.cz001.com.cn/attachement/jpg/site2/20091221/001676c499950c99079e24.jpg\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 554px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p706152\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\tNow the England midfielder Frank Lampard has <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/hint\" target=\"_blank\">hinted</a> that he may <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/retire\" target=\"_blank\">retire</a> from international football after the World Cup in Brazil. He's in Miami with the national squad as they continue their preparations for the <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/tournament\" target=\"_blank\">tournament</a>. Now Lampard will captain the side in Wednesday's friendly against Ecuador. In an interview with the BBC's senior football reporter Ian Dennis, he hinted that the tournament might be his last as an England player. But he began by <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/reflect\" target=\"_blank\">reflecting</a> on his club career with Chelsea after Monday's <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/announcement\" target=\"_blank\">announcement</a> that he is going to leave Stanford Bridge.</p>\n<p>\n\t&quot;You have to move on. OK, I move on, the club moves on, simple as that, and I'm here to <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/concentrate\" target=\"_blank\">concentrate</a> on playing with England, being with England, so much I could <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/relieve\" target=\"_blank\">relieve</a> to say it last night and now I personally, and the team, can really focus on the game, tomorrow and forward, but yes of course, it is a huge thing for me, someday I will probably address more to the Chelsea fans or Chelsea people at another time.&quot;</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(12